<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5 CELLSPACING=0>
<TR><TD><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="ARIAL,HELVETICA" COLOR="#990000"><br><b>The Taxpayer Relief Act of 1997</b></FONT><br>

<FONT SIZE=3 FACE="TIMES">The historic tax law changes just enacted provide unprecedented opportunities for Americans to save more for retirement and education, thus increasing their overall financial security. In recognition of the need to shift away from being a nation of spenders to a nation of savers, the government has given new tax benefits to almost every tax-paying American. The challenge will be to take maximum advantage of this complex new law when pursuing your personal financial strategy.<p>
<font color="#990000" size=2 face="ARIAL,HELVETICA"><b>Key provisions of the law:</b><br></font>
<font face="TIMES" size=2>

The new Roth IRA which creates a tax-free retirement nest egg for eligible taxpayers<p>
The ability to take penalty-free withdrawals from IRAs for important life events such as first home purchase or college education<p>
New types of education savings opportunities, including the "Education IRA"<p>
A capital-gains tax cut to reward long-term investment<p>
Estate tax relief, especially for family-owned businesses<p>
Family tax credits for eligible households with children
</font>
</FONT>
</TR>
</TD>
</TABLE>

</TD>


